org.seedstack.business.domain

Class BaseAggregateRoot<I>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.seedstack.business.domain.BaseEntity<I>
      • org.seedstack.business.domain.BaseAggregateRoot<I>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - The type of the aggregate root identifier.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    AggregateRoot<I>, Entity<I>, Producible

    public abstract class BaseAggregateRoot<I>
extends BaseEntity<I>
implements AggregateRoot<I>
    An helper base class that can be extended to create a domain aggregate root. If extending this base class is not desirable, you can instead do one of the following:
    • Implement AggregateRoot,
    • Annotate your class with DomainAggregateRoot (but this limits the ability to use framework features).
